-- BNP Paribas Wants to Double Its Indian Business by 2010, Les Echos Says
-- B y   S t e v e   R h i n d s
-- 2010-10-28T04:17:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-28/bnp-paribas-wants-to-double-its-indian-business-by-2010-les-echos-says.html
BNP Paribas SA wants to double the
size of its business in India by 2015, Les Echos reported,
citing an interview with Chief Executive Officer Baudouin Prot.  India is expected to contribute 2 percent of the French
bank’s global revenue in five years’ time, up from 1 percent, or
400 million euros, currently, Prot said, according to the daily
newspaper.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Rhinds at 
 srhinds@bloomberg.net  